The paper deals with the fundamentals of parameterized complexity, which is a subfield of computational complexity theory. The paper discusses the definition of parameterization and its relation to polynomial-time computability, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the use of parameterization in the analysis of algorithms and data structures, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of parameterization in the analysis of combinatorial problems, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the use of parameterization in the analysis of logic and proof theory, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Finally, the paper discusses the use of parameterization in the analysis of computational geometry, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG).
